22:09.462 --> 22:11.762
Please.

22:11.764 --> 22:13.564
Spare me
the I-dare-you crap, Cahill.

22:13.566 --> 22:17.535
Everybody knows I can get
anything anywhere anytime.

22:17.537 --> 22:20.371
Just so happens I'm
startin' 5 days of r-and-r.

22:20.373 --> 22:24.542
This time tomorrow I'll be sittin'
on a beach in Hawaii, my friend.

22:24.544 --> 22:26.577
You're getting us the elephant.

22:26.579 --> 22:28.980
Or what?

22:28.981 --> 22:31.382
You gonna still try to hold that
business with the 64th over my head?

22:31.384 --> 22:33.651
Come on. So the pork
was a little off.

22:33.653 --> 22:35.453
A little off?

22:35.455 --> 22:38.489
I know men who spent a week on the
latrine because of that pork.

22:38.491 --> 22:40.624
It's old news, Cahill.

22:40.626 --> 22:41.892
I got too many friends
in high places

22:41.894 --> 22:43.761
to go down for something
small-time like that now.

22:43.763 --> 22:47.565
Oh, I know other things
about you, poole.

22:47.567 --> 22:49.667
Let me tell you
something, Cahill.

22:49.669 --> 22:51.435
There isn't anything you know

22:51.437 --> 22:54.805
that's gonna keep me from gettin'
on that plane to Honolulu.

23:04.751 --> 23:07.585
Doyle: 180 Miles
in the middle of a war.

23:07.587 --> 23:09.387
We can get a truck and drive
it up close to dak nhe.

23:09.389 --> 23:11.455
That'll take about 3 days.

23:11.457 --> 23:12.690
And another day to walk it in.

23:12.692 --> 23:14.592
We'll get there by Friday.

23:14.594 --> 23:16.927
Actually, I was thinking more
along the lines of air travel.

23:16.929 --> 23:18.696
I lined up a cargo plane

23:18.698 --> 23:20.765
to meet us at an airstrip
near ban don, ok?

23:20.767 --> 23:23.100
We fly the elephant down
to this old CIA airstrip

23:23.102 --> 23:24.902
about a 3-hour walk
from dak nhe,

23:24.904 --> 23:26.771
then your montagnard friends
have their elephant

23:26.773 --> 23:28.773
by 2:00 this afternoon, I'm
sitting on the beach in waikiki

23:28.775 --> 23:30.174
in time to see the sunset.

23:30.176 --> 23:34.412
And you wanted a week!
Good job, poole!

23:34.414 --> 23:36.547
We're coming up on ban don now.

23:36.549 --> 23:39.483
There's no place to land
in the rice paddies.

23:39.485 --> 23:42.453
We'll have to go to an I.Z.
Behind the village.

23:42.455 --> 23:43.854
It was real hot here
2 weeks ago.

23:43.856 --> 23:46.424
Probably ok now.

23:46.426 --> 23:48.426
Probably? We're gonna
land on a "probably"?

23:48.428 --> 23:49.660
Lock and load!

24:11.150 --> 24:13.150
Hey, this isn't that bad.

24:13.152 --> 24:15.686
It's kind of peaceful, really.

24:15.688 --> 24:18.556
All right, move out.

24:26.599 --> 24:29.500
Well, Cahill,
you want elephants,

24:29.502 --> 24:31.602
I give you elephants.

24:31.604 --> 24:34.505
Beautiful elephants, I might
add, at no extra cost.

24:34.507 --> 24:35.840
Knowing you, poole,

24:35.842 --> 24:38.843
they're probably big
puppets with men inside.

24:38.845 --> 24:41.479
Let's go.

24:56.596 --> 24:58.162
Y b'ham?

25:01.601 --> 25:03.701
Let me handle the negotiation.

25:03.703 --> 25:05.803
I already talked to
this guy on the radio.

25:05.805 --> 25:09.840
Thinks he's tough, but I'm
gonna crack him like a walnut.

25:35.268 --> 25:37.167
Oh, you're killing me.

25:37.169 --> 25:38.836
What's the problem?

25:38.838 --> 25:40.271
I thought you could
negotiate anything.

25:40.273 --> 25:41.939
I can with leverage. Problem
is we don't have any.

25:41.941 --> 25:43.707
He doesn't care if he sells
the elephant or not.

25:43.709 --> 25:45.276
We don't make his price,
he blows the deal.

25:45.278 --> 25:47.245
What's his price?

25:47.246 --> 25:49.213
Problem number 2.
He wants 60,000 piasters.

25:49.215 --> 25:50.214
The requisition form
captain Doyle gave me

25:50.216 --> 25:51.248
is only good for 50, so...

25:51.250 --> 25:53.784
that's it?
Hell, 10,000 piasters...

25:53.786 --> 25:54.852
that's only about 150 bucks.

25:54.854 --> 25:56.787
We can raise that between us.

25:56.789 --> 25:59.256
No. You tell him 50,000
is our final offer.

25:59.258 --> 26:00.941
We can do it.

26:00.942 --> 26:02.625
Private funds can't be used
for an official purchase

26:02.628 --> 26:04.728
as per regulations.
It's also an order.

26:04.730 --> 26:07.231
Understood? Tell him.

26:08.834 --> 26:13.304
I get it. It's a perfect
way out for you.

26:13.306 --> 26:14.939
You blow the deal,
and the mission is over.

26:14.941 --> 26:18.609
It's what you wanted
from the beginning.

26:18.611 --> 26:21.779
We're going back to the I.Z.
And call for a ride.

26:21.781 --> 26:23.847
Let's go.

26:24.817 --> 26:26.183
Poole, let's move it.

26:26.185 --> 26:28.285
Ok, 50,000.

26:33.960 --> 26:36.727
You're quite
a negotiator, Doyle.

26:39.265 --> 26:43.334
Gracious sir, perhaps now
we could go to the river

26:43.336 --> 26:44.735
and pick our elephant.

26:44.737 --> 26:47.705
River? 50,000 don't
get elephant in river.

26:47.707 --> 26:50.307
50,000 get you Bo-tat.

26:50.309 --> 26:53.210
Bo-tat!

26:56.315 --> 26:57.314
Uh-oh.

27:01.187 --> 27:03.253
Beat it.

27:11.897 --> 27:15.265
Bo-tat is she, not he.

27:15.267 --> 27:17.935
Boy is linh.
Boy go with Bo-tat.

27:17.937 --> 27:21.338
What? No, boy no go
with Bo-tat.

27:21.340 --> 27:23.741
Boy go with Bo-tat.

27:23.743 --> 27:25.275
We're going to a village
far away.

27:25.277 --> 27:26.644
I'm sure linh's family...

27:26.646 --> 27:29.647
boy has no family. All killed.

27:29.649 --> 27:30.881
In the war?

27:30.883 --> 27:33.283
No. Hit by falling star.

27:35.187 --> 27:36.920
Yes, in war.

27:36.922 --> 27:38.922
Which side?

27:38.924 --> 27:40.391
It matter?

27:40.393 --> 27:43.227
I think it's better
if the boy stays here.

27:43.229 --> 27:47.331
He not belong here.
From north, not our people.

27:47.333 --> 27:49.900
We might as well
take him with us.

27:49.902 --> 27:52.236
N-no. We are not
taking a kid with us.

27:52.238 --> 27:53.871
He'll be my responsibility.

27:53.873 --> 27:55.239
No, captain. All right.

27:57.710 --> 27:59.877
Anyone else here know
how to work an elephant?

27:59.879 --> 28:01.445
I was in love with
a fat woman once,

28:01.447 --> 28:02.946
but she never listened to me.

28:02.948 --> 28:06.984
Oh. Mr. Y b'ham,
you must know how

28:06.986 --> 28:08.452
to work an elephant,
right, sir?

28:08.454 --> 28:10.854
I live with elephants
all my life.

28:10.856 --> 28:12.423
I learn nothing?

28:12.425 --> 28:16.860
Is this guy sarcastic,
or is it just me?

28:25.337 --> 28:27.705
Great. Would you like
to come with us, sir?

28:27.707 --> 28:29.740
20,000 piasters.

28:29.742 --> 28:31.241
Deal.

28:31.243 --> 28:33.494
Good job, Doyle.

28:33.495 --> 28:35.746
I think Mr. Y b'ham
would be a wonderful choice.

28:35.748 --> 28:37.214
Just one problem.

28:37.216 --> 28:38.882
What?

28:38.884 --> 28:41.418
He doesn't stare into space
because he's a wise old soul.

28:41.420 --> 28:43.253
He does it because
he's blind as a bat.

28:43.255 --> 28:46.256
Y b'ham not blind.
Y b'ham can...

28:46.258 --> 28:49.359
y b'ham is blind.

28:51.430 --> 28:53.230
10,000 piasters?

29:09.215 --> 29:10.347
Farley: It's a nice view.

29:10.349 --> 29:11.415
Ashford: What nice view?

29:11.417 --> 29:14.918
All I can see
is an elephant's butt.

29:24.463 --> 29:26.230
<i>Parlez-vous francais?</i>

29:27.767 --> 29:29.466
Any luck?

29:29.468 --> 29:32.369
I tried vietnamese,
Cambodian, French,

29:32.371 --> 29:34.271
and 3 dialects of jeh.

29:37.910 --> 29:39.343
Keep an eye on him.

29:39.345 --> 29:41.979
He's on an elephant.
He's hard to miss.

29:41.981 --> 29:44.281
You know what I mean.

29:44.283 --> 29:46.350
We don't know which side
killed his family.

29:46.352 --> 29:48.452
It could've been us.
He might hate Americans.

29:48.454 --> 29:49.987
We don't know, and until we do,

29:49.989 --> 29:51.321
he can't be trusted. Doyle...

29:51.323 --> 29:54.291
he right. Linh
can't be trusted.

29:56.228 --> 29:59.997
Linh no trust Americans.
Americans not trust linh.

29:59.999 --> 30:03.367
Everything's number one, a-ok.

30:25.324 --> 30:27.524
That elephant just came along
to say good-bye, right?

30:27.526 --> 30:29.893
You're not actually thinking
of putting that on my plane?

30:29.895 --> 30:30.894
What's the problem?

30:30.896 --> 30:33.430
What's the problem?

30:33.432 --> 30:34.464
It's an elephant.

30:34.466 --> 30:35.966
Yeah, but, major...

30:35.968 --> 30:37.568
no, no, no. You see,
you cannot put an elephant

30:37.570 --> 30:39.336
on an airplane.

30:39.338 --> 30:41.305
Suppose it starts to panic
and starts moving around?

30:41.307 --> 30:43.473
I lose trim,
the plane goes down.

30:43.475 --> 30:45.008
We all buy the farm.

30:45.010 --> 30:46.577
That's important,
what he just said.

30:46.579 --> 30:48.245
No, no, no.

30:48.247 --> 30:49.847
It's not getting
aboard the plane

30:49.849 --> 30:51.281
unless it's dead.

30:51.283 --> 30:54.451
Now, I'd be happy to oblige...

30:54.453 --> 30:56.486
If you've all grown
too attached to it.

30:56.488 --> 30:57.588
No!

30:57.590 --> 30:59.590
Linh, it's ok.

30:59.592 --> 31:02.226
No one's gonna shoot Bo-tat.

31:04.463 --> 31:05.996
Doyle.

31:10.436 --> 31:12.870
Poole.

31:12.872 --> 31:14.371
Do you have a package

31:14.373 --> 31:16.373
for a Dr. David poole,
d.V.M., on board?

31:16.375 --> 31:17.941
Yeah, I do.

31:24.550 --> 31:27.918
Here we go, gentlemen.
Animal tranquilizer.

31:27.920 --> 31:30.387
She won't move an inch.

31:30.389 --> 31:32.289
Bo-tat's gonna take
a big nap-nap.

31:32.291 --> 31:34.258
Hey, nice try,
but I don't care.

31:34.260 --> 31:36.593
See, my orders say nothing
about lifting an elephant.

31:36.595 --> 31:40.297
Gentlemen, you have a good war.

31:40.299 --> 31:45.002
Ahem, major, maybe
you should read this.

31:46.572 --> 31:49.239
Ok?

31:49.241 --> 31:50.474
This operation's top-secret,

31:50.476 --> 31:51.575
and that's why
you never heard anything

31:51.577 --> 31:53.010
about our large mammal
friend over there.

31:53.012 --> 31:54.544
As a matter of fact,
if anybody asks,

31:54.546 --> 31:57.014
you're moving
a shipment of tuna.

31:57.016 --> 31:58.448
Tuna?

31:58.450 --> 32:00.284
Tuna.

32:02.021 --> 32:03.687
Moving an elephant.

32:03.689 --> 32:06.023
What elephant?

32:11.030 --> 32:12.396
You got 10 minutes.

32:13.565 --> 32:16.333
Gentlemen, I'm responsible
for anything

32:16.335 --> 32:17.601
that goes onto that cargo hold.

32:17.603 --> 32:20.304
Now, if that thing
even twitches,

32:20.306 --> 32:22.472
you're gonna see
an elephant fly.

32:23.976 --> 32:25.309
Hey, that's funny.

32:27.446 --> 32:29.446
All right, yeah.
What's with the letter?

32:29.448 --> 32:32.683
John westmoreland.
Top priority.

32:32.685 --> 32:34.484
Got 8 left.

32:34.486 --> 32:37.287
Now, couldn't get
elephant tranquilizer

32:37.289 --> 32:38.588
'cause the only place
that has it is the London zoo.

32:38.590 --> 32:40.724
It would take too long
to ship, so...

32:40.726 --> 32:42.259
And what's that?

32:42.261 --> 32:44.027
Water buffalo tranquilizer.

32:44.029 --> 32:46.363
It's not as strong,
but my vet guy says

32:46.365 --> 32:49.399
you just give her a little
more, it should work.

32:54.039 --> 32:55.672
My word.

32:55.674 --> 32:58.041
I guess we give her one now,
and then we give her...

32:58.043 --> 32:59.609
One later if she needs it.

32:59.611 --> 33:02.312
How are we supposed to get her
to swallow one of these?

33:02.314 --> 33:04.748
Well... ahem... actually,
according to this,

33:04.750 --> 33:07.384
she's not supposed
to swallow it.

33:09.722 --> 33:12.456
Well, Dr. David poole...

33:12.458 --> 33:14.491
oh, no, no, no, no.

33:14.493 --> 33:16.293
I said I would
help you guys out,

33:16.295 --> 33:18.028
but putting my hand
up an elephant's ass

33:18.030 --> 33:20.297
was never part of the deal, no.

33:20.299 --> 33:21.465
On 3?

33:21.467 --> 33:24.668
Oh... No.

33:24.670 --> 33:27.504
Please, please, please, please.
Ok, what do you have?

33:27.506 --> 33:28.605
Evens. Ok.

33:28.607 --> 33:29.606
1, 2, 3...

33:30.609 --> 33:31.775
Oh.

33:31.777 --> 33:33.610
Heh heh heh heh.

33:35.481 --> 33:39.416
Doyle: Don't you move,
you big suitcase.

33:43.756 --> 33:45.622
Oh, that's horrible.

33:47.693 --> 33:49.593
You weird.

33:51.563 --> 33:53.463
Good thinking, poole.

33:53.465 --> 33:56.033
Well, come on, let's go.

33:56.035 --> 33:59.770
Let's get her on the plane
before this stuff kicks in.

33:59.772 --> 34:01.505
Come on, come on.

34:01.507 --> 34:03.040
Linh thought you joking.

34:03.042 --> 34:05.308
Bo-tat not get on plane.

34:08.313 --> 34:09.478
Excuse me?

34:09.481 --> 34:11.748
Bo-tat no like be on plane.

34:13.619 --> 34:14.751
How often does she fly?

34:14.753 --> 34:17.286
Bo-tat no like plane.

34:17.289 --> 34:18.755
The kid's right.
Let's get a truck.

34:18.757 --> 34:20.757
The plane is here.
We're taking the plane.

34:20.759 --> 34:22.492
Bo-tat no like plane.

34:22.494 --> 34:23.827
Kid... I'll handle it.

34:23.829 --> 34:25.429
Well, then handle it.

34:25.431 --> 34:27.264
Hurry up.
She goes down out here,

34:27.266 --> 34:28.532
you'll never get her inside.

34:28.534 --> 34:30.534
Linh... you nice American?

34:30.536 --> 34:32.402
You think you number one?

34:32.404 --> 34:35.572
You number 10.
You all number 10.

34:35.574 --> 34:36.739
Cahill!

34:45.317 --> 34:46.483
Bo-tat...

34:47.518 --> 34:49.753
that's the way. Come on.

34:58.430 --> 34:59.629
Heads up.

34:59.631 --> 35:01.264
You number 10.

35:01.266 --> 35:02.499
Tell her to lie down.

35:02.500 --> 35:03.733
What'd you do to Bo-tat?

35:03.735 --> 35:06.336
Tell her to lie down
so she doesn't hurt herself.

35:29.428 --> 35:31.761
Tko. Heh heh heh.

35:33.332 --> 35:35.365
What'd you do?

35:35.367 --> 35:37.634
She's ok, linh. She's not dead.

35:37.636 --> 35:40.270
You killed everything.
You killed everything.

35:40.272 --> 35:41.705
You killed Bo-tat.

35:41.707 --> 35:43.440
She's not dead.

35:43.442 --> 35:45.342
You killed Bo-tat.
You killed Bo-tat.

35:45.344 --> 35:47.811
You make it die.
You killed Bo-tat.

35:47.813 --> 35:49.779
You killed Bo-tat.

35:51.817 --> 35:53.450
Cahill: She's fine.

35:56.355 --> 35:58.321
She's just sleeping.

36:01.760 --> 36:03.360
¶ Your love ¶

36:03.362 --> 36:06.363
¶ is lifting me higher ¶

36:06.365 --> 36:08.365
¶ than I've ever ¶

36:08.367 --> 36:10.800
¶ been lifted before ¶

36:10.802 --> 36:12.869
¶ so keep it up ¶

36:12.871 --> 36:16.439
¶ quench my desire ¶

36:16.441 --> 36:20.844
¶ and I'll be at your side
forevermore ¶

36:20.846 --> 36:22.512
¶ you know, your love ¶

36:22.514 --> 36:24.281
¶ your love keeps lifting me ¶

36:24.283 --> 36:25.649
¶ on lifting ¶

36:25.651 --> 36:28.451
h.A., what's the first thing
you're gonna do

36:28.453 --> 36:29.653
when you get home?

36:29.655 --> 36:30.787
First thing?

36:30.789 --> 36:33.757
Hug my mom and
give her a big kiss.

36:33.759 --> 36:35.358
Second thing.

36:35.360 --> 36:38.628
Second thing?
Get her some kleenex.

36:38.630 --> 36:40.430
She gonna be bawling
her eyes out.

36:40.432 --> 36:41.581
So what about you, captain?

36:41.582 --> 36:42.731
What's waiting for you
back in the world?

36:42.734 --> 36:44.534
Uh...

36:46.438 --> 36:47.604
A hammer.

36:48.640 --> 36:50.607
My brother's
got a roofing company

36:50.609 --> 36:51.875
in fort lauderdale.

36:51.877 --> 36:54.778
Wants me to be a part
of that. Can't wait.

36:54.780 --> 37:00.350
Been dressed in green too long.
Time to get a real life.

37:04.356 --> 37:05.555
Ahh...

37:10.529 --> 37:12.662
Hey, hey, hey, hey,
what are you kissing?

37:12.664 --> 37:14.364
What is that?

37:14.366 --> 37:16.666
Oh, it's nothing.

37:16.668 --> 37:18.501
Come on, what is it?

37:18.503 --> 37:20.537
It's stupid. It's, uh...

37:20.539 --> 37:22.639
When I first got to 'nam,

37:22.641 --> 37:25.875
I was in the main administration
building in da nang,

37:25.877 --> 37:30.447
feeling scared and...
Nervous like we all do

37:30.449 --> 37:32.349
and thinking about home.

37:32.351 --> 37:34.651
I was walking past
this coke machine,

37:34.653 --> 37:36.519
a bottle of coke
just dropped down,

37:36.521 --> 37:38.888
so...

37:38.890 --> 37:42.759
Drank that bottle of coke
and kept the cap for luck.

37:43.729 --> 37:45.362
So has it worked?

37:45.364 --> 37:47.564
Well, I don't really
believe in that stuff,

37:47.566 --> 37:49.633
but, you know...
2 years without a scratch.

37:49.635 --> 37:50.900
Who knows?

37:50.902 --> 37:51.901
I'll buy it.

37:51.903 --> 37:54.304
Nah, man, I couldn't.

37:54.306 --> 37:56.840
Come on, $20. I'll buy it.

37:56.842 --> 37:58.575
Keep your money, man. I...

37:58.577 --> 38:00.644
$40.

38:00.646 --> 38:03.880
Well, hell, if it means
that much to you, I mean...

38:03.882 --> 38:07.450
he just got it off the bottle
he's been drinking.

38:09.655 --> 38:11.655
Captain,

38:11.657 --> 38:13.890
major wants a word with you.

38:15.827 --> 38:19.362
Hey, farley, look at this
great big beautiful beast.

38:19.364 --> 38:21.364
How can you not like
something like that?

38:21.366 --> 38:22.365
Well, sir, I tell you...

38:22.367 --> 38:23.366
uhh... ow.

38:23.368 --> 38:25.635
Yeah?

38:25.637 --> 38:28.371
Yeah, we got a nasty headwind.

38:28.373 --> 38:31.474
Give baby the other
dose, captain.

38:35.914 --> 38:37.547
Poole,

38:37.549 --> 38:40.750
we have to give
the elephant the second pill...

38:40.752 --> 38:41.785
farley had a little run-in

38:41.787 --> 38:43.653
with the second pill, captain.

38:49.461 --> 38:51.728
Well, how much longer
will she stay out?

38:51.730 --> 38:53.230
Well, one of these
things is supposed

38:53.231 --> 38:54.731
to knock out a water
buffalo for 6 hours.

38:54.733 --> 38:56.366
And Bo-tat's about the size
of 3 water buffaloes...

38:56.368 --> 38:58.335
how much longer
do we have, poole?

38:58.337 --> 39:00.670
We got another hour, easy.

39:00.672 --> 39:03.673
Ok.

39:14.886 --> 39:18.555
I, uh...

39:18.557 --> 39:20.490
I was using the metric system.

39:29.901 --> 39:31.101
Tell me you did that.

39:32.871 --> 39:34.404
Uhh.

39:36.675 --> 39:39.109
Doyle: Whoa!

39:48.687 --> 39:50.687
It's awake!

39:50.689 --> 39:51.654
What was your first clue?

