47:28.346 --> 47:31.380
H.A. Is going home soon, linh.

47:31.382 --> 47:33.883
He wants good luck to make
sure he gets there safe.

47:33.885 --> 47:36.452
You want good luck?

47:36.454 --> 47:37.920
Don't tell me,

47:37.922 --> 47:39.488
you have an ancient
vietnamese bottle cap

47:39.490 --> 47:41.357
you're willing to sell me.

47:41.359 --> 47:44.260
Linh not sell anything.

47:44.262 --> 47:46.996
Here, elephant is good luck.

47:48.566 --> 47:52.468
You want good luck,
you touch Bo-tat.

47:53.571 --> 47:56.339
Yeah, right.

47:59.444 --> 48:00.977
So what's bad luck?

48:00.979 --> 48:03.646
Um, don't whistle in dark.

48:03.648 --> 48:05.548
Snake will come out
and bite you.

48:05.550 --> 48:07.583
Snakes?

48:07.585 --> 48:09.285
It get worse.

48:09.287 --> 48:10.453
Yeah?

48:10.455 --> 48:13.022
If you see owl at night,

48:13.024 --> 48:15.324
someone in your family die.

48:15.326 --> 48:17.460
Wow. So that's the worst?

48:17.462 --> 48:19.295
No. No?

48:19.297 --> 48:21.597
Owl nothing compared to crow.

48:21.599 --> 48:23.499
You see crow any time,

48:23.501 --> 48:25.935
that very, very bad luck.

48:25.937 --> 48:27.570
So what happens
when you see a crow?

48:27.572 --> 48:29.472
I tell you,

48:29.474 --> 48:31.641
if you see a big black bird,

48:31.643 --> 48:33.542
you run away.

48:38.449 --> 48:40.016
You know what?

48:40.018 --> 48:41.984
This country's
really beautiful.

48:41.986 --> 48:44.287
I mean, I am shocked.

48:44.289 --> 48:46.289
Yeah, it is great, isn't it?

48:46.291 --> 48:47.223
Kind of reminds me of home.

48:47.225 --> 48:48.357
Oh, yeah?

48:48.359 --> 48:49.592
They got a lot of rice paddies

48:49.594 --> 48:51.260
in cornpone, lowa,
do they, farley?

48:51.262 --> 48:52.662
Oh, no, that's Arkansas.

48:52.664 --> 48:54.363
I just meant... you meant what?

48:54.365 --> 48:55.698
Tell me exactly what you meant.

48:55.699 --> 48:57.032
Tell me exactly what
it is about this place

48:57.035 --> 48:58.267
that reminds you of home, huh?

48:58.269 --> 49:00.236
What is it?

49:00.238 --> 49:01.504
The spirit-crushing humidity?

49:01.506 --> 49:02.605
The disease-bearing insects?

49:02.607 --> 49:04.407
Or is it the special feeling

49:04.409 --> 49:06.242
that comes from the knowledge
that at any given moment,

49:06.244 --> 49:08.511
a sniper's bullet could come
spiraling towards your forehead?

49:08.513 --> 49:10.947
Is that it?

49:10.949 --> 49:13.983
Poole, I'm getting this weird
feeling you don't like it here.

49:13.985 --> 49:15.251
What's wrong with you?

49:15.253 --> 49:18.487
I love it. Everybody loves it.

49:18.489 --> 49:20.356
Bet you're the only
American in Vietnam

49:20.358 --> 49:22.024
who would rather
be someplace else.

49:22.026 --> 49:23.025
Enough.

49:31.402 --> 49:32.735
Hey! Hey, come on!

49:32.737 --> 49:34.603
Gimme... gi...

49:34.605 --> 49:37.239
ohh.

49:37.241 --> 49:39.041
Let's keep moving.

49:41.245 --> 49:43.379
Where are you going? Hey!

49:43.381 --> 49:45.414
They're going to help.

49:45.416 --> 49:49.251
For the love of... Cahill,
don't get me wrong.

49:49.253 --> 49:50.619
I would like nothing more

49:50.621 --> 49:52.555
than to skip through the
countryside doing good deeds,

49:52.557 --> 49:53.990
but we don't have the time.

49:53.992 --> 49:55.725
We have to get
a truck, remember?

49:55.727 --> 49:57.593
It won't take long.

49:57.595 --> 49:59.996
Besides, we might even
get something out of it.

50:03.401 --> 50:05.601
Maybe they'll
give you the stump.

50:07.305 --> 50:08.671
You go play good samaritan,

50:08.673 --> 50:12.675
I'm going to go to the
road and do our job, ok?

50:12.677 --> 50:16.012
Go. Go play. Go play.

50:38.736 --> 50:40.269
Bye, now.

50:40.271 --> 50:41.838
Doyle: Where is everyone?

50:41.839 --> 50:43.406
They'll be back in a minute.

50:44.776 --> 50:46.308
Big stump.

50:46.310 --> 50:48.411
America won something today,

50:48.413 --> 50:50.613
and we didn't even
have to shoot anyone.

50:50.615 --> 50:52.481
Oh, yeah?
Well, we lost 2 hours,

50:52.483 --> 50:54.817
and we still don't
have ourselves a truck, so...

50:54.819 --> 50:59.055
Yeah. How about an old diesel
with a 16-foot flatbed?

50:59.057 --> 51:00.097
You think that ought to do?

51:07.765 --> 51:11.333
One of our developing
agencies gave them a truck.

51:11.335 --> 51:12.768
But they rarely can afford gas,

51:12.770 --> 51:15.337
